in for next... that's about it <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulimbas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>limbas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/27/02 9:46:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4554.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bracer of Benevolence</span><hr size=1> Hehe, anyone have an estimate of how many hp he has, and how hard he hits, as I know he is unslowable...Oh and has anyone tried that disease based shammy slow?  I think it is called...Plague of Insects <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/upanamah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Panamah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/27/02 10:52:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4554.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bracer of Benevolence</span><hr size=1> We don't bother to try to cast on him.  I guess Wizard lures will work.  He hits for 200-ish I think.  He's not slowable.  It's a pretty long fight.  But I have done this with 5 characters (rogue, cleric, warrior (59), druid, enchanter).  All enchanter could really do is speed/c3. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udarjeeling.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Darjeeling</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/27/02 11:28:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4554.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bracer of Benevolence</span><hr size=1> Can slow with PoI. Not sure if it's worth it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uarnoldjay.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arnoldjay</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/28/02 6:57:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4554.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bracer of Benevolence</span><hr size=1> When you are preparing to pull, have a second player stand on the hill over the tunnel watching for roamers - often Glati, Cargalia and wolves roam nearby and the last thing you want is a dragon add. Once they give you the all-clear, tag him and walk him carefully in to the tunnel to SG. Don't cut the tunnel corner or he may warp under the world. Keep him boxed centrally in the tunnel during the fight. <br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uewanakanach0king.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ewan aka nach0king</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/28/02 8:59:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4554.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bracer of Benevolence</span><hr size=1> Our last scout was done with a bit of a spartan force (Rogue, Monk, Cleric, Cleric, Warrior, Wizard, Wizard) and they commented that Lures were pretty much the only thing worth casting. Other than that... just defensive tank, and kill it. He doesn't hit phenomanally hard but he *does* have a barrel load of HP, so it's a long fight without high damage output. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukelkun.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kelkun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/28/02 10:07:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4554.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bracer of Benevolence</span><hr size=1> <br>Killed him with a 60 war, 60 cle, 60 mag and 60 druid.<br><br>Took a while, but wasn't a hard fight.  Just sight the war there and CH him.<br><br>Mage had Velk boots and epic, which helped alot.  Fire DD seemed to work just fine.  He was tashed/Mala/Malosinied.<br><br>Kelkun <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usanadan1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sanadan1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/29/02 3:32:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4554.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bracer of Benevolence</span><hr size=1> Hits for 260.  About twice or three times the hp of a protector of zek (so 50-70k hp maybe, including his regen).  Everything else previously stated is of course quite accurate.  This is a very simple quest for an excellent item. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showPrevMessage?topicID=4554.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showNextMessage?topicID=4554.topi